Please be careful of messing around with header formats. "Japanese people" and "Koreans" should NOT be under "Ainu people".

Wang's paper was published BEFORE Cooke's with the latter discussing about Kofun strand while the prior not. Also, Cooke's research is redundant information that can be found in main article dedicated to Genetic and anthropometric studies on Japanese people and is thus trimmed down.

Do not reinterpret what the paper (Wang 2021) clearly stated: Japanese populations can be modelled as deriving from Korean (91%) and  Jomon (9%). Jomon's ancestry was not "significant" at all. Also, please be aware of grammatical errors. Edit with caution.

The description of the map is too long as it breaks readability (meaning, it intrudes other headings significantly). The description seems to contain the exact same information, so there is no real need to keep all the information for the sake of just keeping it.
